<br>
I'm not trying to start a Mac/PC war here, I'm just interested. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A few people always seem to get pissed off when this topic comes up/ I'll try to answer the question without doing that.<br>
<br>
coloursync-when you take your pict to a company, mostly the colours will not be the same. In print, it is very important that doesn't happen and companies use coloursync to prevent colour shifts. <br>
<br>
Macs are an graphics design industry standard, or at least they are according to the KVB college guy. <br>
<br>
OS X- os X is very stable (a bit like windows XP if you've ever used that). MacOs9 is stable in most cases, but one program can crash the system which forces you to reboot, just like older versions of windows.<br>
<br>
According to benchmark tests, a G4 can outperform a same speed PC in MFLOPS (millions of floating point operations per second). <br>
<br>
I don't know if the swapping of disks is a big thing, but i'm pretty sure you can get programs for windows that let you swap with a mac. <br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub84.ezboard.com/bprojectk"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.liquid2k.com/projectk/projectklink.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=koji150>koji150</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.koji150.8m.com/koji.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/02 11:35:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11441.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>    Re: bleh</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> What's the big thing about using Macs for graphic design? Is it just because everyone in the industry uses macs (which can read PC discs anyway) or what? Is there some huge advantage over PCs in that section, or not?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Today it's a myth that started a few years back, but was true then.  Macs used to have the advantage over x86 machines because good graphic software was primarily made for Apple.  But now with today's industry standard apps being made for both platforms, this inequality has been erased. <br>
<br>
If you were to compare a Mac and a x86 machine side by side, the only difference you'd see is the brightness.  Macs have a slightly brighter output than PCs do.  I've noticed in Adobe Gamma you can set the brightness standard at either Mac or Windows and you can see the difference there.  <br>
<br>
As for colors being messed up, this can happen on any platform.  Monitors need to be calibrated to best represent what is outputted in print.  A problem I see with Macs today is the push for LCD screens, which <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>cannot</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be calibrated and therefore often misrepresent colors.  Eventually LCD technology will meet up with CRT and this will no longer be a problem.<br>
<br>
As for now it's really just a personal preference.  Also, it seems like artsy people are drawn to Macs, for what reason I don't know.  <br>
<br>
I have used both Mac and PC OSs and I prefer Windows 2000 Professional.  It's stable and it runs what I want it to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgabriel3>Lord Gabriel 3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/1/02 5:05:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11441.topic&index=29>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/dogfuchow/pie.jpg height=120 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:  Re: bleh</span><hr size=1> Actually, Colorsync works with my LCD screen, and no complaints on printing from me. <br>
